notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger; title in Zacour-Hirsch is Psalter.
Upper outer corner of f. [i] cut out.

msContents.summary: Breviary, use of the Franciscans of Avignon; includes calendar (f. 1r-6v), litany (f. 39r-41v) with names of saints venerated in Provençe and Office for the Dead (f. 146v-158v).

supportDesc.extent: 166 leaves : 149 x 100 (100 x 62) mm. bound to 155 x 107 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Parchment; ii (18th-century paper) + 167 + ii (18th-century paper); [i], [1-166], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 22-24 long lines; ruled in lead.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in Gothic book script in a single hand, except for a middle section (f. 50r-81v) in a second hand; headings and marginal notations in a later hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: 4-line puzzle initial (f. 1r); 8-line puzzle initial with red penwork ornamentation (f. 50r); rubricated throughout, with red used for headings, initials and capitals; some capitals stroked with yellow.
Decorated initial, Initial D, Face, f. 35r [=36r]

binding.p: 18th-century French calf, mistakenly titled Diurna[l] de Marsei[lle] on spine.

origin.p: Written in Avignon in the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Arms of Michel de Léon, treasurer of France at Marseilles (1727-1800) on spine; monogram of Charles Kothen (1814-1880), a Finnish nobleman who was a refugee in Marseilles, on paper endleaf.
Sold by Laurence Witten (New Haven, Conn.), 1958.
